{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858126740,"sessionID":"ses_2869e5ba1ffeMCunfKql4U6jqU","part":{"id":"prt_d79648b08001qvA49NSjlq44aP","messageID":"msg_d796481f300139DDJ0hzAik6KP","sessionID":"ses_2869e5ba1ffeMCunfKql4U6jqU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_88b3ab1ccb9a4ee38b981b90","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024 вҖ” DockerService е°ҒиЈ… вҖ” Design\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: `DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`) жҳҜ AgentCube CLI зҡ„ Docker е®ҲжҠӨиҝӣзЁӢдәӨдә’еұӮпјҢе°ҒиЈ… `docker` SDK for PythonпјҲ`docker>=6.0.0`пјүпјҢжҸҗдҫӣй•ңеғҸжһ„е»әгҖҒжҺЁйҖҒгҖҒзҷ»еҪ•гҖҒжү“ж ҮгҖҒдҝЎжҒҜжҹҘиҜўе’Ңжё…зҗҶиғҪеҠӣгҖӮе®ғиў« `BuildRuntime`пјҲжң¬ең° Docker жһ„е»әпјүе’Ң `PublishRuntime`пјҲжң¬ең°й•ңеғҸжҺЁйҖҒиҮі RegistryпјүзӣҙжҺҘи°ғз”ЁгҖӮ\n6: \n7: **Scope**: иЎҘе…Ё spec дёӯе®ҡд№үдҪҶеҪ“еүҚе®һзҺ°зјәеӨұзҡ„ж–№жі•пјҲ`get_image_info`гҖҒ`_get_image_info`гҖҒ`remove_image`пјүпјҢдҝ®жӯЈдёҺ spec дёҚдёҖиҮҙзҡ„зӯҫеҗҚпјҲ`push_image`гҖҒ`_docker_login_sdk`гҖҒ`_tag_image_sdk` зҡ„иҝ”еӣһеҖјзұ»еһӢпјүпјҢе№¶е®Ңе–„й”ҷиҜҜеӨ„зҗҶгҖӮ\n8: \n9: **Size**: M вҖ” зәҰ 60 иЎҢж–°еўһд»Јз Ғ + зӯҫеҗҚи°ғж•ҙ + жөӢиҜ•иҰҶзӣ–гҖӮ\n10: \n11: ---\n12: \n13: ## Architecture\n14: \n15: ```\n16: в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n17: в”Ӯ                     CLI Commands                         в”Ӯ\n18: в”Ӯ  pack в”Ӯ build в”Ӯ publish в”Ӯ invoke в”Ӯ status               в”Ӯ\n19: в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n20:            в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ\n21:     в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ            в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n22:     в”ӮBuildRuntime в”Ӯ            в”ӮPublishRuntimeв”Ӯ\n23:     в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ            в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n24:            в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ\n25:            в”Ӯ  check_docker_available()в”Ӯ\n26:            в”Ӯ  build_image()           в”Ӯ  check_docker_available()\n27:            в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ  _docker_login_sdk()\n28:            в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ  push_image()\n29:            в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n30:                       в”Ӯ\n31:               в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n32:               в”Ӯ DockerService в”Ӯ\n33:               в”Ӯ               в”Ӯ\n34:               в”Ӯ docker.from_  в”Ӯ\n35:               в”Ӯ    env()      в”Ӯ\n36:               в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n37:                       в”Ӯ\n38:               в”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв–јв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\n39:               в”Ӯ  Docker SDK   в”Ӯ\n40:               в”Ӯ  (docker-py)  в”Ӯ\n41:               в””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n42: ```\n43: \n44: **Design principles**:\n45: - жҜҸж¬Ўж–№жі•и°ғз”ЁзӢ¬з«ӢеҲӣе»ә `docker.from_env()` е®ўжҲ·з«ҜпјҲж— зҠ¶жҖҒгҖҒзәҝзЁӢе®үе…ЁгҖҒйҒҝе…Қй•ҝиҝһжҺҘжі„жјҸпјү\n46: - жүҖжңүе…¬е…ұж–№жі•иҝ”еӣһ `Dict[str, Any]` жҲ– `bool`пјҢејӮеёёеҗ‘дёҠдј ж’ӯз”ұ Runtime еұӮжҚ•иҺ·\n47: - `_` еүҚзјҖж–№жі•дёәеҶ…йғЁиҫ…еҠ©пјҢдёҚдҫӣеӨ–йғЁзӣҙжҺҘи°ғз”Ё\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## Component Design\n52: \n53: ### `DockerService.__init__(verbose: bool = False)`\n54: \n55: еӯҳеӮЁ `verbose` ж Үеҝ—пјҢз”ЁдәҺеҗҺз»ӯеҸҜйҖүзҡ„иҜҰз»Ҷж—Ҙеҝ—иҫ“еҮәпјҲеҪ“еүҚе®һзҺ°дёӯ verbose жңӘдё»еҠЁдҪҝз”ЁпјҢдҝқз•ҷжҺҘеҸЈд»ҘеҢ№й…Қе…¶д»– Service зҡ„дёҖиҮҙжҖ§пјүгҖӮ\n56: \n57: ### `check_docker_available() -> bool`\n58: \n59: йҖҡиҝҮ `docker.from_env()` еҲӣе»әе®ўжҲ·з«Ҝе№¶и°ғз”Ё `client.ping()`гҖӮд»»дҪ•ејӮеёёпјҲиҝһжҺҘеӨұиҙҘгҖҒжқғйҷҗдёҚи¶ігҖҒе®ҲжҠӨиҝӣзЁӢжңӘиҝҗиЎҢпјүиҝ”еӣһ `False`гҖӮ\n60: \n61: **Current**: вң… е·Іе®һзҺ°пјҢз¬ҰеҗҲ specгҖӮ\n62: \n63: ### `build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag, build_args) -> Dict[str, str]`\n64: \n65: и°ғз”Ё `client.images.build()` жү§иЎҢжһ„е»әпјҢиҝ”еӣһеҢ…еҗ« `image_name`гҖҒ`image_id`пјҲshort_idпјүгҖҒ`image_size`пјҲдәәзұ»еҸҜиҜ»ж јејҸпјүгҖҒ`build_time`пјҲз§’ж•°пјҢдҝқз•ҷдёӨдҪҚе°Ҹж•°пјүзҡ„еӯ—е…ёгҖӮ\n66: \n67: `build_args` з”ЁдәҺдј йҖ’д»ЈзҗҶи®ҫзҪ®пјҲеҰӮ `HTTP_PROXY`/`HTTPS_PROXY`пјүпјҢзӣҙжҺҘйҖҸдј з»ҷ Docker SDK зҡ„ `buildargs` еҸӮж•°гҖӮ\n68: \n69: **Current**: вң… е·Іе®һзҺ°пјҢз¬ҰеҗҲ specгҖӮ\n70: \n71: ### `get_image_info(image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]`\n72: \n73: иҺ·еҸ–жң¬ең°й•ңеғҸзҡ„е…ғдҝЎжҒҜгҖӮе…¬е…ұж–№жі•пјҢеҶ…йғЁе§”жүҳз»ҷ `_get_image_info`гҖӮ\n74: \n75: иҝ”еӣһеӯ—е…ёеҢ…еҗ«пјҡ\n76: - `image_id`: е®Ңж•ҙ SHA256 ID\n77: - `short_id`: жҲӘзҹӯзҡ„ IDпјҲ`sha256:xxxxx`пјү\n78: - `size`: дәәзұ»еҸҜиҜ»еӨ§е°ҸпјҲеҰӮ `50.0 MB`пјү\n79: - `tags`: й•ңеғҸе…іиҒ”зҡ„ж ҮзӯҫеҲ—иЎЁ\n80: - `created`: еҲӣе»әж—¶й—ҙеӯ—з¬ҰдёІ\n81: \n82: **Current**: вқҢ зјәеӨұпјҢйңҖж–°еўһгҖӮ\n83: \n84: ### `_get_image_info(image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]`\n85: \n86: еҶ…йғЁе®һзҺ°пјҡйҖҡиҝҮ `client.images.get(image_name)` иҺ·еҸ– `Image` еҜ№иұЎпјҢд»Һ `attrs` дёӯжҸҗеҸ–е…ғж•°жҚ®е№¶ж јејҸеҢ–гҖӮ\n87: \n88: **Current**: вқҢ зјәеӨұпјҢйңҖж–°еўһгҖӮ\n89: \n90: ### `_format_size(size_bytes: int) -> str`\n91: \n92: е°Ҷеӯ—иҠӮж•°ж јејҸеҢ–дёәдәәзұ»еҸҜиҜ»еӯ—з¬ҰдёІгҖӮйҳҲеҖјпјҡ`<1024` вҶ’ `B`пјҢ`<1MB` вҶ’ `KB`пјҢ`<1GB` вҶ’ `MB`пјҢ`>=1GB` вҶ’ `GB`гҖӮ\n93: \n94: **Current**: вң… е·Іе®һзҺ°пјҢз¬ҰеҗҲ specгҖӮ\n95: \n96: ### `push_image(image_name, registry_url, username, password) -> Dict[str, str]`\n97: \n98: е°Ҷжң¬ең°й•ңеғҸжҺЁйҖҒиҮі RegistryгҖӮ\n99: \n100: **Spec зӯҫеҗҚ**пјҲдёҺеҪ“еүҚе®һзҺ°дёҚеҗҢпјү:\n101: ```python\n102: def push_image(\n103:     self,\n104:     image_name: str,\n105:     registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n106:     username: Optional[str] = None,\n107:     password: Optional[str] = None,\n108: ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n109: ```\n110: \n111: **еҪ“еүҚзӯҫеҗҚ**:\n112: ```python\n113: def push_image(\n114:     self,\n115:     image_tag: str,          # е®Ңж•ҙж ҮзӯҫеҰӮ registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0\n116:     registry_url: str,       # еҝ…еЎ«\n117:     username: Optional[str] = None,\n118:     password: Optional[str] = None,\n119: ) -> Dict[str, str]: ...\n120: ```\n121: \n122: **йңҖиҰҒи°ғж•ҙ**: е°Ҷ `push_image` зӯҫеҗҚж”№дёә spec е®ҡд№үзҡ„ `image_name` + еҸҜйҖү `registry_url`пјҢеҶ…йғЁйҖ»иҫ‘пјҡ\n123: 1. еҰӮжһңжҸҗдҫӣ `registry_url`пјҢе…Ҳи°ғз”Ё `_tag_image_sdk` е°Ҷ `image_name` жү“зӣ®ж Үж Үзӯҫ\n124: 2. еҰӮжһңжҸҗдҫӣ `username` е’Ң `password`пјҢи°ғз”Ё `_docker_login_sdk` зҷ»еҪ•\n125: 3. и°ғз”Ё `client.images.push()` жҺЁйҖҒпјҢжөҒејҸеӨ„зҗҶж—Ҙеҝ—пјҲеҪ“еүҚжңӘж¶Ҳиҙ№ push иҝ”еӣһеҖјдёӯзҡ„жөҒејҸж—Ҙеҝ—пјү\n126: 4. иҝ”еӣһ `{\"pushed_image\": <full_tag>, \"push_time\": \"<n.nn>s\"}`пјҲspec иҰҒжұӮиҝ”еӣһ `pushed_image` е’Ң `push_time`пјү\n127: \n128: **Current**: вҡ пёҸ е·Іе®һзҺ°дҪҶзӯҫеҗҚдёҺ spec дёҚдёҖиҮҙпјҢиҝ”еӣһеҖјзјәе°‘ `push_time`гҖӮ\n129: \n130: ### `_docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password) -> None`\n131: \n132: йҖҡиҝҮ `client.login()` зҷ»еҪ• RegistryгҖӮ\n133: \n134: **Spec иҝ”еӣһеҖј**: `None`\n135: **еҪ“еүҚиҝ”еӣһеҖј**: `bool`пјҲиҝ”еӣһ `True`пјү\n136: \n137: **йңҖиҰҒи°ғж•ҙ**: иҝ”еӣһеҖјж”№дёә `None`пјҢеӨұиҙҘж—¶и®© `docker.errors.APIError` еҗ‘дёҠдј ж’ӯгҖӮ\n138: \n139: **Current**: вҡ пёҸ е·Іе®һзҺ°дҪҶиҝ”еӣһеҖјзұ»еһӢдёҺ spec дёҚдёҖиҮҙгҖӮ\n140: \n141: ### `_tag_image_sdk(source_image, target_image) -> None`\n142: \n143: е°Ҷжң¬ең°й•ңеғҸд»Һ `source_image` жү“ж Үдёә `target_image`гҖӮ\n144: \n145: **Spec иҝ”еӣһеҖј**: `None`\n146: **еҪ“еүҚиҝ”еӣһеҖј**: `bool`пјҲиҝ”еӣһ `True`пјү\n147: \n148: **йңҖиҰҒи°ғж•ҙ**: иҝ”еӣһеҖјж”№дёә `None`гҖӮ\n149: \n150: **Current**: вҡ пёҸ е·Іе®һзҺ°дҪҶиҝ”еӣһеҖјзұ»еһӢдёҺ spec дёҚдёҖиҮҙгҖӮ\n151: \n152: ### `remove_image(image_name: str) -> bool`\n153: \n154: еҲ йҷӨжң¬ең° Docker й•ңеғҸгҖӮжҲҗеҠҹиҝ”еӣһ `True`пјӣеӨұиҙҘж—¶и®°еҪ• warning ж—Ҙеҝ—е№¶иҝ”еӣһ `False`гҖӮ\n155: \n156: дҪҝз”Ё `client.images.remove(image_name)` жү§иЎҢеҲ йҷӨгҖӮжҚ•иҺ· `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` е’Ң `docker.errors.APIError`пјҢи®°еҪ• warning еҗҺиҝ”еӣһ `False`гҖӮ\n157: \n158: **Current**: вқҢ зјәеӨұпјҢйңҖж–°еўһгҖӮ\n159: \n160: ---\n161: \n162: ## Data Flow Details\n163: \n164: ### Build жөҒзЁӢ\n165: \n166: ```\n167: BuildRuntime._build_local()\n168:   в”ңв”Җв”Җ DockerService.check_docker_available()  вҶ’ bool\n169:   в””в”Җв”Җ DockerService.build_image()\n170:         в”ңв”Җв”Җ docker.from_env()\n171:         в”ңв”Җв”Җ client.images.build(path, dockerfile, tag, buildargs)\n172:         в”ңв”Җв”Җ client.images.get(image.id)       вҶ’ иҺ·еҸ– Size\n173:         в””в”Җв”Җ return {image_name, image_id, image_size, build_time}\n174: ```\n175: \n176: ### Publish жөҒзЁӢпјҲlocal build modeпјү\n177: \n178: ```\n179: PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()\n180:   в”ңв”Җв”Җ DockerService.check_docker_available()  вҶ’ bool\n181:   в”ңв”Җв”Җ DockerService._docker_login_sdk()       вҶ’ None (if credentials)\n182:   в””в”Җв”Җ DockerService.push_image()\n183:         в”ңв”Җв”Җ docker.from_env()\n184:         в”ңв”Җв”Җ client.images.push(repository, tag, auth_config)\n185:         в””в”Җв”Җ return {pushed_image, push_time}\n186: ```\n187: \n188: ---\n189: \n190: ## Error Handling\n191: \n192: | еңәжҷҜ | ејӮеёёзұ»еһӢ | еӨ„зҗҶж–№ејҸ |\n193: |------|----------|----------|\n194: | Docker е®ҲжҠӨиҝӣзЁӢдёҚеҸҜиҫҫ | `docker.errors.DockerException` | `check_docker_available()` иҝ”еӣһ `False`пјӣе…¶д»–ж–№жі•еҗ‘дёҠдј ж’ӯ |\n195: | й•ңеғҸдёҚеӯҳеңЁ | `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` | `remove_image()` иҝ”еӣһ `False` + warningпјӣе…¶д»–ж–№жі•еҗ‘дёҠдј ж’ӯ |\n196: | жһ„е»әеӨұиҙҘ | `docker.errors.BuildError` | еҗ‘дёҠдј ж’ӯпјҢз”ұ `BuildRuntime` / CLI `_handle_error` жҚ•иҺ· |\n197: | Registry и®ӨиҜҒеӨұиҙҘ | `docker.errors.APIError` | `_docker_login_sdk()` еҗ‘дёҠдј ж’ӯпјӣ`push_image()` еҗ‘дёҠдј ж’ӯ |\n198: | жҺЁйҖҒеӨұиҙҘ | `docker.errors.APIError` | еҗ‘дёҠдј ж’ӯпјҢз”ұ `PublishRuntime` / CLI жҚ•иҺ· |\n199: | жқғйҷҗдёҚи¶і | `docker.errors.APIError` (403) | еҗ‘дёҠдј ж’ӯ |\n200: \n201: **е…ій”®зәҰжқҹ**: `DockerService` жң¬иә«дёҚжү“еҚ°й”ҷиҜҜдҝЎжҒҜжҲ–и°ғз”Ё `sys.exit()` вҖ” жүҖжңүејӮеёёеҗ‘дёҠдј ж’ӯпјҢз”ұ Runtime еұӮжҲ– CLI `_handle_error` з»ҹдёҖеӨ„зҗҶгҖӮ\n202: \n203: ---\n204: \n205: ## Testing Strategy\n206: \n207: ### зҺ°жңүжөӢиҜ•иҰҶзӣ–пјҲ`tests/services/test_docker_service.py`пјү\n208: \n209: | жөӢиҜ•зұ» | иҰҶзӣ–ж–№жі• | зҠ¶жҖҒ |\n210: |--------|----------|------|\n211: | `TestDockerServiceCheckDockerAvailableRunning` | `check_docker_available` (success) | вң… |\n212: | `TestDockerServiceCheckDockerAvailableNotRunning` | `check_docker_available` (failure) | вң… |\n213: | `TestDockerServiceBuildImageSuccess` | `build_image` (success) | вң… |\n214: | `TestDockerServiceBuildImageWithProxy` | `build_image` (with buildargs) | вң… |\n215: | `TestDockerServiceBuildImageFailure` | `build_image` (error propagation) | вң… |\n216: | `TestDockerServiceFormatSize*` | `_format_size` (B/KB/MB/GB) | вң… |\n217: | `TestDockerService_PushImage_Success` | `push_image` (success) | вҡ пёҸ йңҖжӣҙж–°ж–ӯиЁҖ |\n218: | `TestDockerService_PushImage_WithCredentials` | `push_image` (auth) | вҡ пёҸ йңҖжӣҙж–°ж–ӯиЁҖ |\n219: | `TestDockerService_PushImage_Failure` | `push_image` (APIError) | вҡ пёҸ йңҖжӣҙж–°ж–ӯиЁҖ |\n220: | `TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Success` | `_docker_login_sdk` (success) | вҡ пёҸ йңҖжӣҙж–°ж–ӯиЁҖ |\n221: | `TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Failure` | `_docker_login_sdk` (APIError) | вҡ пёҸ йңҖжӣҙж–°ж–ӯиЁҖ |\n222: | `TestDockerService_TagImageSdk_Success` | `_tag_image_sdk` (success) | вҡ пёҸ йңҖжӣҙж–°ж–ӯиЁҖ |\n223: \n224: ### йңҖж–°еўһжөӢиҜ•\n225: \n226: | жөӢиҜ•зұ» | иҰҶзӣ–ж–№жі• | еңәжҷҜ |\n227: |--------|----------|------|\n228: | `TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo` | `get_image_info` | еӯҳеңЁй•ңеғҸпјҢиҝ”еӣһе®Ңж•ҙе…ғдҝЎжҒҜ |\n229: | `TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo` | `get_image_info` | й•ңеғҸдёҚеӯҳеңЁпјҢжҠӣеҮә `ImageNotFound` |\n230: | `TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo` | `_get_image_info` | еҶ…йғЁе®һзҺ°йӘҢиҜҒ |\n231: | `TestDockerServiceRemoveImage` | `remove_image` | жҲҗеҠҹеҲ йҷӨиҝ”еӣһ `True` |\n232: | `TestDockerServiceRemoveImage` | `remove_image` | й•ңеғҸдёҚеӯҳеңЁиҝ”еӣһ `False` + warning |\n233: | `TestDockerServiceRemoveImage` | `remove_image` | API й”ҷиҜҜиҝ”еӣһ `False` + warning |\n234: | `TestDockerServicePushImageSpec` | `push_image` | ж–°зӯҫеҗҚпјҡ`image_name` + `registry_url` |\n235: | `TestDockerServicePushImageSpec` | `push_image` | ж—  `registry_url` ж—¶зӣҙжҺҘжҺЁйҖҒжң¬ең°ж Үзӯҫ |\n236: | `TestDockerServicePushImageSpec` | `push_image` | иҝ”еӣһ `push_time` |\n237: \n238: ### Mock зӯ–з•Ҙ\n239: \n240: жүҖжңүжөӢиҜ•йҖҡиҝҮ `patch(\"agentcube.services.docker_service.docker.from_env\")` жЁЎжӢҹ Docker е®ўжҲ·з«ҜпјҢдёҚдҫқиө–зңҹе®һ Docker е®ҲжҠӨиҝӣзЁӢгҖӮ\n241: \n242: ---\n243: \n244: ## Implementation Notes\n245: \n246: ### зӯҫеҗҚеҸҳжӣҙеҪұе“ҚеҲҶжһҗ\n247: \n248: `push_image` зӯҫеҗҚеҸҳжӣҙдјҡеҪұе“Қд»ҘдёӢи°ғз”Ёж–№пјҡ\n249: \n250: 1. **`PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()`** (`publish_runtime.py:105`):\n251:    ```python\n252:    # Before:\n253:    result = docker_service.push_image(image_tag, registry_url or \"\", username, password)\n254:    # After:\n255:    result = docker_service.push_image(image_tag, registry_url or \"\", username, password)\n256:    ```\n257:    и°ғз”Ёж–№дј йҖ’зҡ„з¬¬дёҖдёӘеҸӮж•°жҳҜе®Ңж•ҙ `image_tag`пјҲеҰӮ `registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0`пјүпјҢеңЁж–°зӯҫеҗҚдёӯдҪңдёә `image_name` дҪҝз”ЁгҖӮеҰӮжһң `registry_url` дёәз©әеӯ—з¬ҰдёІпјҢдёҚиҝӣиЎҢйҮҚж–°жү“ж ҮпјҢзӣҙжҺҘжҺЁйҖҒгҖӮиЎҢдёәе…је®№гҖӮ\n258: \n259: 2. **жөӢиҜ•ж–Үд»¶** (`test_docker_service.py`): йңҖжӣҙж–°ж–ӯиЁҖд»ҘеҢ№й…Қж–°иҝ”еӣһеҖјпјҲ`push_time` жӣҝд»Ј `status`пјүгҖӮ\n260: \n261: ### иҝ”еӣһеҖјзұ»еһӢеҸҳжӣҙ\n262: \n263: `_docker_login_sdk` е’Ң `_tag_image_sdk` зҡ„иҝ”еӣһеҖјд»Һ `bool` ж”№дёә `None`гҖӮз”ұдәҺе®ғд»¬жҳҜ `_` еүҚзјҖзҡ„еҶ…йғЁж–№жі•пјҢдё”и°ғз”Ёж–№дёҚжЈҖжҹҘиҝ”еӣһеҖјпјҲ`publish_runtime.py:103` и°ғз”Ё `_docker_login_sdk` дҪҶжңӘдҪҝз”Ёиҝ”еӣһеҖјпјүпјҢжӯӨеҸҳжӣҙдёәе®үе…ЁгҖӮ\n264: \n265: ### зјәеӨұж–№жі•е®һзҺ°иҰҒзӮ№\n266: \n267: **`get_image_info` / `_get_image_info`**:\n268: ```python\n269: def _get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n270:     client = docker.from_env()\n271:     image = client.images.get(image_name)\n272:     attrs = image.attrs\n273:     return {\n274:         \"image_id\": image.id,\n275:         \"short_id\": image.short_id,\n276:         \"size\": self._format_size(int(attrs.get(\"Size\", 0) or 0)),\n277:         \"tags\": \", \".join(image.tags) if image.tags else \"<none>\",\n278:         \"created\": attrs.get(\"Created\", \"unknown\"),\n279:     }\n280: \n281: def get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]:\n282:     return self._get_image_info(image_name)\n283: ```\n284: \n285: **`remove_image`**:\n286: ```python\n287: def remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool:\n288:     import logging\n289:     logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n290:     try:\n291:         client = docker.from_env()\n292:         client.images.remove(image_name)\n293:         return True\n294:     except (docker.errors.ImageNotFound, docker.errors.APIError) as e:\n295:         logger.warning(\"Failed to remove image %s: %s\", image_name, e)\n296:         return False\n297: ```\n298: \n299: **`push_image` зӯҫеҗҚи°ғж•ҙ**:\n300: ```python\n301: def push_image(\n302:     self,\n303:     image_name: str,\n304:     registry_url: Optional[str] = None,\n305:     username: Optional[str] = None,\n306:     password: Optional[str] = None,\n307: ) -> Dict[str, str]:\n308:     import time\n309:     client = docker.from_env()\n310:     start_time = time.time()\n311: \n312:     if registry_url:\n313:         # Determine target tag\n314:         parts = image_name.rsplit(\":\", 1)\n315:         repo = parts[0]\n316:         tag = parts[1] if len(parts) > 1 else \"latest\"\n317:         target = f\"{registry_url}/{repo}:{tag}\"\n318:         self._tag_image_sdk(image_name, target)\n319:         push_repo = f\"{registry_url}/{repo}\"\n320:         push_tag = tag\n321:     else:\n322:         parts = image_name.rsplit(\":\", 1)\n323:         push_repo = parts[0]\n324:         push_tag = parts[1] if len(parts) > 1 else \"latest\"\n325: \n326:     auth_config = None\n327:     if username and password:\n328:         auth_config = {\"username\": username, \"password\": password}\n329:         self._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)\n330: \n331:     client.images.push(push_repo, tag=push_tag, auth_config=auth_config)\n332:     push_time = time.time() - start_time\n333:     return {\"pushed_image\": image_name, \"push_time\": f\"{push_time:.2f}s\"}\n334: ```\n\n(End of file - total 334 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024 вҖ” DockerService е°ҒиЈ… вҖ” Design\n\n## Overview\n\n`DockerService` (`agentcube/services/docker_service.py`) жҳҜ AgentCube CLI зҡ„ Docker е®ҲжҠӨиҝӣзЁӢдәӨдә’еұӮпјҢе°ҒиЈ… `docker` SDK for PythonпјҲ`docker>=6.0.0`пјүпјҢжҸҗдҫӣй•ңеғҸжһ„е»әгҖҒжҺЁйҖҒгҖҒзҷ»еҪ•гҖҒжү“ж ҮгҖҒдҝЎжҒҜжҹҘиҜўе’Ңжё…зҗҶиғҪеҠӣгҖӮе®ғиў« `BuildRuntime`пјҲжң¬ең° Docker жһ„е»әпјүе’Ң `PublishRuntime`пјҲжң¬ең°й•ңеғҸжҺЁйҖҒиҮі RegistryпјүзӣҙжҺҘи°ғз”ЁгҖӮ\n\n**Scope**: иЎҘе…Ё spec дёӯе®ҡд№үдҪҶеҪ“еүҚе®һзҺ°зјәеӨұзҡ„ж–№жі•пјҲ`get_image_info`гҖҒ`_get_image_info`гҖҒ`remove_image`пјүпјҢдҝ®жӯЈдёҺ spec дёҚдёҖиҮҙзҡ„зӯҫеҗҚпјҲ`push_image`гҖҒ`_docker_login_sdk`гҖҒ`_tag_image_sdk` зҡ„иҝ”еӣһеҖјзұ»еһӢпјүпјҢе№¶е®Ңе–„й”ҷиҜҜеӨ„зҗҶгҖӮ\n\n**Size**: M вҖ” зәҰ 60 иЎҢж–°еўһд»Јз Ғ + зӯҫеҗҚи°ғж•ҙ + жөӢиҜ•иҰҶзӣ–гҖӮ\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\nв”Ңв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”җ\nв”Ӯ                     CLI Commands                         в”Ӯ\nв”Ӯ  pack в”Ӯ build в”Ӯ publish в”Ӯ invoke в”Ӯ status               в”Ӯ\nв””в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”¬в”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n           в”Ӯ                          в”Ӯ","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/design.md","time":{"start":1775858126728,"end":1775858126737}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858128090,"sessionID":"ses_2869e5ba1ffeMCunfKql4U6jqU","part":{"id":"prt_d79649017001eljbrb3IiHAxFi","messageID":"msg_d796481f300139DDJ0hzAik6KP","sessionID":"ses_2869e5ba1ffeMCunfKql4U6jqU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_e8d2b4d302e34d7789fd938a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-024: DockerService е°ҒиЈ… вҖ” Delta Spec\n2: \n3: ## Context\n4: \n5: - **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n6: - **Language:** Python\n7: - **Size:** M\n8: - **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n9: \n10: ## Delta Requirements\n11: \n12: ### Requirement: DockerService initialization\n13: \n14: The system SHALL provide a `DockerService` class that encapsulates Docker SDK operations, initialized with an optional `verbose` flag.\n15: \n16: #### Scenario: Default initialization\n17: - **GIVEN** `DockerService()` is called with no arguments\n18: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n19: - **THEN** `self.verbose` SHALL be `False` and a Docker client SHALL be initialized via `docker.from_env()`\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Verbose initialization\n22: - **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose=True)` is called\n23: - **WHEN** the instance is created\n24: - **THEN** `self.verbose` SHALL be `True` and the logger SHALL be configured for debug-level output\n25: \n26: ### Requirement: Docker availability check\n27: \n28: The system SHALL verify that the Docker daemon is running and reachable before attempting build or push operations.\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: Docker is available\n31: - **GIVEN** the Docker daemon is running and accessible\n32: - **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True`\n34: \n35: #### Scenario: Docker is unavailable\n36: - **GIVEN** the Docker daemon is not running or the SDK cannot connect\n37: - **WHEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called\n38: - **THEN** it SHALL catch `docker.errors.DockerException` (or connection errors) and return `False`\n39: \n40: ### Requirement: Build image\n41: \n42: The system SHALL build a Docker image from a Dockerfile and context path, with optional build arguments and a configurable tag.\n43: \n44: #### Scenario: Build with default tag\n45: - **GIVEN** a valid `dockerfile_path` and `context_path`\n46: - **WHEN** `build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, \"my-agent\")` is called\n47: - **THEN** it SHALL build the image tagged `my-agent:latest` and return a dict with keys `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n48: \n49: #### Scenario: Build with custom tag\n50: - **GIVEN** a valid workspace\n51: - **WHEN** `build_image(..., image_name=\"my-agent\", tag=\"v1.2.3\")` is called\n52: - **THEN** the image SHALL be tagged `my-agent:v1.2.3`\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: Build with build arguments\n55: - **GIVEN** `build_args={\"PIP_INDEX_URL\": \"https://proxy.example.com/simple\"}` is passed\n56: - **WHEN** `build_image` is called\n57: - **THEN** the Docker build SHALL receive `buildargs` containing the provided key-value pairs\n58: \n59: #### Scenario: Build failure\n60: - **GIVEN** the Dockerfile contains a syntax error or a build step fails\n61: - **WHEN** `build_image` is called\n62: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with a message describing the build failure\n63: \n64: #### Scenario: Build records elapsed time\n65: - **GIVEN** a build is initiated\n66: - **WHEN** `build_image` completes successfully\n67: - **THEN** the returned dict SHALL include `build_time` as a formatted duration string (e.g., `\"12.34s\"`)\n68: \n69: ### Requirement: Image info retrieval\n70: \n71: The system SHALL retrieve metadata about a local Docker image, including its ID and human-readable size.\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Image exists locally\n74: - **GIVEN** an image `my-agent:latest` exists in the local Docker daemon\n75: - **WHEN** `get_image_info(\"my-agent:latest\")` is called\n76: - **THEN** it SHALL return a dict with keys `image_id` and `image_size` (human-readable, e.g., `\"256.5 MB\"`)\n77: \n78: #### Scenario: Image does not exist\n79: - **GIVEN** no image named `nonexistent:latest` exists locally\n80: - **WHEN** `get_image_info(\"nonexistent:latest\")` is called\n81: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `ValueError` with a message indicating the image was not found\n82: \n83: ### Requirement: Size formatting\n84: \n85: The system SHALL convert byte counts to human-readable size strings.\n86: \n87: #### Scenario: Bytes\n88: - **GIVEN** a size of `512` bytes\n89: - **WHEN** `_format_size(512)` is called\n90: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"512 B\"`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Megabytes\n93: - **GIVEN** a size of `1048576` bytes (1 MiB)\n94: - **WHEN** `_format_size(1048576)` is called\n95: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"1.0 MB\"`\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: Gigabytes\n98: - **GIVEN** a size of `1073741824` bytes (1 GiB)\n99: - **WHEN** `_format_size(1073741824)` is called\n100: - **THEN** it SHALL return `\"1.0 GB\"`\n101: \n102: ### Requirement: Push image\n103: \n104: The system SHALL push a local Docker image to a registry, optionally authenticating and retagging.\n105: \n106: #### Scenario: Push without registry URL\n107: - **GIVEN** a local image `my-agent:v1.0.0` exists\n108: - **WHEN** `push_image(\"my-agent:v1.0.0\")` is called with no `registry_url`\n109: - **THEN** it SHALL push the image to its existing tag and return a dict with `pushed_image` and `push_time`\n110: \n111: #### Scenario: Push with registry URL and credentials\n112: - **GIVEN** `registry_url=\"registry.example.com\"`, `username`, and `password` are provided\n113: - **WHEN** `push_image(\"my-agent:v1.0.0\", registry_url, username, password)` is called\n114: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n115:   1. Login to the registry via `_docker_login_sdk`\n116:   2. Retag the image to `{registry_url}/my-agent:v1.0.0` via `_tag_image_sdk`\n117:   3. Push the retagged image\n118:   4. Return `pushed_image` as the full registry-prefixed tag\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Push without credentials\n121: - **GIVEN** `registry_url` is provided but `username` or `password` is `None`\n122: - **WHEN** `push_image` is called\n123: - **THEN** it SHALL skip the login step and attempt to push using existing Docker credentials\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Push failure\n126: - **GIVEN** the registry is unreachable or authentication fails\n127: - **WHEN** `push_image` is called\n128: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with a message describing the push failure\n129: \n130: #### Scenario: Push records elapsed time\n131: - **GIVEN** a push is initiated\n132: - **WHEN** `push_image` completes successfully\n133: - **THEN** the returned dict SHALL include `push_time` as a formatted duration string\n134: \n135: ### Requirement: Docker login\n136: \n137: The system SHALL authenticate to a Docker registry using the Docker SDK.\n138: \n139: #### Scenario: Successful login\n140: - **GIVEN** valid `registry`, `username`, and `password`\n141: - **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password)` is called\n142: - **THEN** it SHALL call `client.login()` with the provided credentials and succeed without raising\n143: \n144: #### Scenario: Login failure\n145: - **GIVEN** invalid credentials or unreachable registry\n146: - **WHEN** `_docker_login_sdk` is called\n147: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with the login error message\n148: \n149: ### Requirement: Image tagging\n150: \n151: The system SHALL retag a local Docker image.\n152: \n153: #### Scenario: Successful tag\n154: - **GIVEN** source image `my-agent:v1.0.0` exists\n155: - **WHEN** `_tag_image_sdk(\"my-agent:v1.0.0\", \"registry.example.com/my-agent:v1.0.0\")` is called\n156: - **THEN** the target tag SHALL exist in the local Docker daemon\n157: \n158: #### Scenario: Tag failure\n159: - **GIVEN** the source image does not exist\n160: - **WHEN** `_tag_image_sdk` is called\n161: - **THEN** it SHALL raise `RuntimeError` with the tagging error message\n162: \n163: ### Requirement: Remove image\n164: \n165: The system SHALL remove a local Docker image and handle failures gracefully.\n166: \n167: #### Scenario: Successful removal\n168: - **GIVEN** image `my-agent:old` exists locally\n169: - **WHEN** `remove_image(\"my-agent:old\")` is called\n170: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True` and the image SHALL no longer be listed locally\n171: \n172: #### Scenario: Removal failure\n173: - **GIVEN** image `my-agent:in-use` is referenced by a running container or does not exist\n174: - **WHEN** `remove_image(\"my-agent:in-use\")` is called\n175: - **THEN** it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n176: \n177: ### Requirement: Verbose logging during operations\n178: \n179: The system SHALL emit detailed logs during Docker operations when `verbose=True`.\n180: \n181: #### Scenario: Verbose build logging\n182: - **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose=True)`\n183: - **WHEN** `build_image` is called\n184: - **THEN** it SHALL log the Dockerfile path, context path, image name, tag, and any build arguments\n185: \n186: #### Scenario: Verbose push logging\n187: - **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose=True)`\n188: - **WHEN** `push_image` is called with credentials\n189: - **THEN** it SHALL log the registry URL, username (not password), and target image name\n190: \n191: ## File changes\n192: \n193: | Action | File | Description |\n194: |--------|------|-------------|\n195: | Add | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | DockerService class with build, push, info, remove operations |\n196: | Add | `tests/services/test_docker_service.py` | DockerService unit tests |\n\n(End of file - total 196 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-024: DockerService е°ҒиЈ… вҖ” Delta Spec\n\n## Context\n\n- **Module:** `cmd/cli`\n- **Language:** Python\n- **Size:** M\n- **Base specs:** `cli-toolkit/design.md`, `cli-toolkit/spec.md`\n\n## Delta Requirements\n\n### Requirement: DockerService initialization\n\nThe system SHALL provide a `DockerService` class that encapsulates Docker SDK operations, initialized with an optional `verbose` flag.\n\n#### Scenario: Default initialization\n- **GIVEN** `DockerService()` is called with no arguments\n- **WHEN** the instance is created\n- **THEN** `self.verbose` SHALL be `False` and a Docker client SHALL be initialized via `docker.from_env()`\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775858128082,"end":1775858128089}}}}
