{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775858191243,"sessionID":"ses_2869e5ba1ffeMCunfKql4U6jqU","part":{"id":"prt_d7964fc5b00142bLq5xhyiCsEd","messageID":"msg_d7964b324001Cs4c1yBM53lH5P","sessionID":"ses_2869e5ba1ffeMCunfKql4U6jqU","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"call_779d1dbd5bc249b183c61420","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-024 вҖ” DockerService е°ҒиЈ… вҖ” Tasks\n\n> **Module:** cmd/cli\n> **Language:** Python\n> **Size:** M\n> **Precondition:** Stage ST-3 (Design) completed\n> **Reference:** `changes/AR-024/proposal.md`, `changes/AR-024/design.md`, `changes/AR-024/delta-spec.md`\n> **Dependency:** None\n\n## T1. Fix `_docker_login_sdk` return type: `bool` вҶ’ `None`\n\n- [ ] Change `_docker_login_sdk` return type annotation from `-> bool` to `-> None`\n- [ ] Remove `return True` statement; let `client.login()` result fall through\n- [ ] Update docstring to reflect `None` return\n- [ ] Write test: successful login returns `None` (no exception raised)\n- [ ] Write test: login failure raises `docker.errors.APIError` (propagates upward)\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Success -v` passes with `None` assertion\n\n---\n\n## T2. Fix `_tag_image_sdk` return type: `bool` вҶ’ `None`\n\n- [ ] Change `_tag_image_sdk` return type annotation from `-> bool` to `-> None`\n- [ ] Remove `return True` statement; let `image.tag()` result fall through\n- [ ] Update docstring to reflect `None` return\n- [ ] Write test: successful tagging returns `None` (no exception raised)\n- [ ] Write test: tagging failure (source image not found) raises `docker.errors.ImageNotFound`\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerService_TagImageSdk_Success -v` passes with `None` assertion\n\n---\n\n## T3. Implement `_get_image_info` (internal helper)\n\n- [ ] Add `_get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]` method\n- [ ] Create `docker.from_env()` client inside method\n- [ ] Call `client.images.get(image_name)` to retrieve `Image` object\n- [ ] Extract `image_id` (full ID), `short_id`, `size` (via `_format_size`), `tags` (comma-joined or `\"<none>\"`), `created` from `image.attrs`\n- [ ] Return dict with keys: `image_id`, `short_id`, `size`, `tags`, `created`\n- [ ] Write test: image exists вҶ’ returns dict with all five keys populated correctly\n- [ ] Write test: image not found вҶ’ `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` propagates upward\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo -v` passes\n\n---\n\n## T4. Implement `get_image_info` (public method)\n\n- [ ] Add `get_image_info(self, image_name: str) -> Dict[str, str]` method\n- [ ] Delegate to `self._get_image_info(image_name)`\n- [ ] Write test: delegates to `_get_image_info` and returns result\n- [ ] Write test: image not found вҶ’ `ValueError` with descriptive message (per delta-spec)\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo -v` passes; public method wraps internal correctly\n\n---\n\n## T5. Implement `remove_image`\n\n- [ ] Add `remove_image(self, image_name: str) -> bool` method\n- [ ] Create `docker.from_env()` client inside method\n- [ ] Call `client.images.remove(image_name)`; return `True` on success\n- [ ] Catch `docker.errors.ImageNotFound` вҶ’ log warning, return `False`\n- [ ] Catch `docker.errors.APIError` вҶ’ log warning, return `False`\n- [ ] Write test: image exists вҶ’ returns `True`, `client.images.remove` called once\n- [ ] Write test: image not found вҶ’ returns `False`, warning logged\n- [ ] Write test: API error (e.g., image in use) вҶ’ returns `False`, warning logged\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServiceRemoveImage -v` passes\n\n---\n\n## T6. Fix `push_image` signature and implementation\n\n- [ ] Change first parameter from `image_tag: str` to `image_name: str`\n- [ ] Change `registry_url: str` to `registry_url: Optional[str] = None`\n- [ ] Add `import time` (if not already present at top of method)\n- [ ] Record `start_time = time.time()` at method entry\n- [ ] If `registry_url` is provided:\n  - Parse `image_name` to extract repo and tag\n  - Build target tag: `{registry_url}/{repo}:{tag}`\n  - Call `self._tag_image_sdk(image_name, target)`\n  - Set `push_repo` and `push_tag` from target\n- [ ] If `registry_url` is not provided:\n  - Parse `image_name` to extract repo and tag\n  - Set `push_repo` and `push_tag` directly\n- [ ] If `username` and `password` provided, call `self._docker_login_sdk(registry_url, username, password)`\n- [ ] Call `client.images.push(push_repo, tag=push_tag, auth_config=...)`\n- [ ] Compute `push_time = time.time() - start_time`\n- [ ] Return `{\"pushed_image\": image_name, \"push_time\": f\"{push_time:.2f}s\"}`\n- [ ] Update docstring to match new signature and return value\n- [ ] Write test: push without `registry_url` вҶ’ pushes directly, returns `pushed_image` + `push_time`\n- [ ] Write test: push with `registry_url` and credentials вҶ’ tags, logs in, pushes, returns full tag\n- [ ] Write test: push with `registry_url` but no credentials вҶ’ skips login, pushes\n- [ ] Write test: push failure вҶ’ `docker.errors.APIError` propagates upward\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py::TestDockerServicePushImageSpec -v` passes\n\n---\n\n## T7. Update `PublishRuntime` caller for new `push_image` signature\n\n- [ ] Read `publish_runtime.py` to identify `push_image` call site(s)\n- [ ] Update call to match new signature: `push_image(image_name, registry_url, username, password)`\n- [ ] Verify caller does not depend on old return keys (`status` вҶ’ now `push_time`)\n- [ ] Write test: `PublishRuntime._prepare_local_image()` works with new `push_image` signature (mocked `DockerService`)\n\n**Verification:** `pytest tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v` passes; no `TypeError` from signature mismatch\n\n---\n\n## T8. Update existing tests for signature/return changes\n\n- [ ] Update `TestDockerService_PushImage_Success` assertions: expect `push_time` key instead of `status`\n- [ ] Update `TestDockerService_PushImage_WithCredentials` assertions: match new signature and return\n- [ ] Update `TestDockerService_PushImage_Failure` assertions: verify `APIError` propagation\n- [ ] Update `TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Success` assertion: expect `None` return instead of `True`\n- [ ] Update `TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Failure` assertion: verify `APIError` propagation\n- [ ] Update `TestDockerService_TagImageSdk_Success` assertion: expect `None` return instead of `True`\n\n**Verification:** All existing `test_docker_service.py` tests pass with updated assertions\n\n---\n\n## T9. Lint, type-check, coverage gate\n\n- [ ] `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py` вҖ” no violations\n- [ ] `ruff check cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/publish_runtime.py` вҖ” no violations\n- [ ] `mypy cmd/cli/agentcube/` вҖ” no type errors\n- [ ] `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py -v` вҖ” all pass\n- [ ] `pytest tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v` вҖ” all pass\n- [ ] `pytest tests/ --cov=agentcube.services.docker_service --cov-report=term-missing` вҖ” coverage вүҘ 90%\n\n**Verification:** All lint/type-check/test commands pass with zero errors\n\n---\n\n## Task Dependencies\n\n```\nT1 в”Җв”Җв”җ\nT2 в”Җв”Җв”јв”Җв”Җ T6 в”Җв”Җ T7 в”Җв”Җ T9\n     в”Ӯ           в”Ӯ\nT3 в”Җв”Җв”Ө           в”Ӯ\nT4 в”Җв”Җв”Ө           в”Ӯ\nT5 в”Җв”Җв”Ө           в”Ӯ\n     в”Ӯ           в”Ӯ\nT8 в”Җв”Җв”ҙв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”Җв”ҳ\n```\n\n## Parallelizable Groups\n\n| Group | Tasks | Prerequisites |\n|-------|-------|---------------|\n| G1 | T1, T2, T3, T5 | None (independent method changes) |\n| G2 | T4 | T3 |\n| G3 | T6 | T1, T2 |\n| G4 | T7, T8 | T6 |\n| G5 | T9 | T4, T5, T7, T8 |\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n| # | Criterion | Command |\n|---|-----------|---------|\n| AC1 | `get_image_info` returns dict with `image_id`, `short_id`, `size`, `tags`, `created` | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerServiceGetImageInfo -v` |\n| AC2 | `remove_image` returns `True` on success, `False` + warning on failure | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerServiceRemoveImage -v` |\n| AC3 | `push_image` accepts `image_name` + optional `registry_url`, returns `pushed_image` + `push_time` | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerServicePushImageSpec -v` |\n| AC4 | `_docker_login_sdk` returns `None` (not `bool`) | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerService_DockerLoginSdk_Success -v` |\n| AC5 | `_tag_image_sdk` returns `None` (not `bool`) | `pytest tests/...::TestDockerService_TagImageSdk_Success -v` |\n| AC6 | `PublishRuntime` caller updated and functional | `pytest tests/runtime/test_publish_runtime.py -v` |\n| AC7 | All existing tests pass with updated assertions | `pytest tests/services/test_docker_service.py -v` |\n| AC8 | Lint and type-check pass | `ruff check` + `mypy` with zero violations |\n| AC9 | Test coverage вүҘ 90% for `docker_service.py` | `pytest --cov=agentcube.services.docker_service` |\n","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-024/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/docker_service.py\">\nERROR [47:40] Argument of type \"str | None\" cannot be assigned to parameter \"name\" of type \"str\" in function \"get\"\nВ В Type \"str | None\" is not assignable to type \"str\"\nВ В В В \"None\" is not assignable to \"str\"\n</diagnostics>\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/cmd/cli/agentcube/services/metadata_service.py\">\nERROR [101:24] Arguments missing for parameters \"description\", \"region\", \"version\", \"imag